 types of ellipsis known as conjunction reduction and gapping found in coordinate structures. Chapter 3 discusses elements seemingly exhibiting coordination-like properties, such as dan 'than' in comparative constructions like Jan is groter dan zij 'Jan is taller than she'.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aDutch languagexSyntax. 4aDutch and The Netherlands. 4aLanguage and Literature. 4aLinguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Syntax.2bisacsh  aDutch, syntax, coordination, ellipsis.1 aCorver, Norbert, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2019z978311066152140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048542895zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048542895zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048542895.jpg  a978-3-11-066152-1 AUP eBook Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA